summary: This document provides detailed information on how to view aircraft records, including the types of files contained on a CD Rom, the format of the records, and the organization of documents within those records. It outlines the various document types related to airworthiness and registration, as well as the procedures for accessing and interpreting these records.
keyFacts: The document explains the structure and content of aircraft records available on CD Rom.
It details the types of documents included, such as airworthiness files and registration files.
The document outlines how to navigate the records using Adobe Acrobat Reader.
It mentions that documents exceeding 17 inches in length are segmented for clarity.
There are references to protective orders affecting certain paragraphs of the document.
